{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σίγλος</b> <br /> or <b>σίκλος</b> (the latter form in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX, 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus, and 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus (see. below))\">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>], ὁ,= Hebrew <b>shekel</b>, a weight [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(LXX.Exo.30.23, +others) or coin [prev. work](LXX.Lev.5.15)\">LXX</a>]; δραχμὴ μία τὸ ἥμισυ τοῦ σ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.Exo.39.2 (38.26); but ὁ σ... Ἀττικὰς δέχεται δραχμὰς τέτταρας 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 3.8.2, compare 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus see at {σίκλος}. \">LXX+1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> the Persian ς. was the  1/3000th part of the Baby lonian silver talent, half the silver stater of Asia Minor, and = 7 1/2 <i>Attic dialect</i> ὀβολοί, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.5.6; or 8 ὀβολοί, _accusative_ to 9th c.AD: Photius Legal icographus, etc., quoting 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 1094 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (perhaps erroneously, instead of for sense [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>ear-ring</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9th c.AD: Photius Legal icographus, etc., compare {σιγλοφόρος} \">Refs 9th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 34.8.7, probably corrupt for Σικελικός. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9079","accentedUnicode":"σίκλος","shortDef":"a shekel","mediumDef":"a shekel","stepGloss":"a shekel","stepTransliteration":"siklos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}